might be recorded.

00:41:21.660 --> 00:41:25.060
My question is, if you were
an artist and you hit Rome,

00:41:25.060 --> 00:41:27.600
would you stop by this
famous art school?

00:41:27.600 --> 00:41:29.200
I mean, I think you
would, right?

00:41:29.200 --> 00:41:32.450
And so they could've
met maybe there,

00:41:32.450 --> 00:41:35.260
certainly Brumidi would've
gone down to the Bay of Naples,

00:41:35.260 --> 00:41:37.360
Zahn was hanging out
there with, you know,

00:41:37.360 --> 00:41:38.970
admittedly other artists.

00:41:38.970 --> 00:41:43.230
But still, I want to see if
that's a rabbit hole I would

00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:46.580
like to do go down to see
if I can find some way

00:41:46.580 --> 00:41:48.580
that they are connected,
if they are connected

00:41:48.580 --> 00:41:52.800
or knew one another
or met one another.

00:41:52.800 --> 00:41:54.100
So that's one idea.

00:41:54.100 --> 00:41:59.040
The other thing that I need to
do some more work on is I would

00:41:59.040 --> 00:42:04.600
like to see if I can
understand the circumstances

00:42:04.600 --> 00:42:08.570
under which the Library of
Congress acquired those volumes.

00:42:08.570 --> 00:42:12.110
So it turns out, right,
that there are notes

00:42:12.110 --> 00:42:14.590
